This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the search and retrieval of information from the web. It also involves the use of search engines, which is a common topic in this sub-category. 

The paper may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves the use of language processing techniques to extract information from the web. 

The Database (cs.DB) sub-category is also a likely fit as the paper deals with the storage and retrieval of information from databases. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is a possible fit as the paper may involve the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the search results and identify potential drug leads. 

The Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category is also a possible fit as the paper may involve the development of software tools to facilitate the search and retrieval of information from the web.
